m\": \"a time\", \"from\": 3266, \"to\": 3272}, {\"ngram\": \"unrest\", \"from\": 3276, \"to\": 3282}, {\"ngram\": \"rioting\", \"from\": 3284, \"to\": 3291}, {\"ngram\": \"protest\", \"from\": 3296, \"to\": 3303}, {\"ngram\": \"many pockets\", \"from\": 3307, \"to\": 3319}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The remnants of Team GB still in Paris will return on the Eurostar on Mondaywith a haul of 65 medals, largely in line with the past three Games.\", \"from\": 3332, \"to\": 3476, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3348, \"end\": 3355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4284691412764676e-20, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 3365, \"end\": 3370, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4495731047582816e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3390, \"end\": 3398, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"score\": 0.9999999971996658, \"rank\": 2.800266309394127e-09, \"text\": \"Eurostar\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The remnants\", \"from\": 3332, \"to\": 3344}, {\"ngram\": \"Mondaywith\", \"from\": 3402, \"to\": 3412}, {\"ngram\": \"a haul\", \"from\": 3413, \"to\": 3419}, {\"ngram\": \"65 medals\", \"from\": 3423, \"to\": 3432}, {\"ngram\": \"line\", \"from\": 3445, \"to\": 3449}, {\"ngram\": \"the past three Games\", \"from\": 3455, \"to\": 3475}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And, yet, there is a slight nagging sense of the ones that got away for the likes of Josh Kerr and Matt Hudson-Smith on the track, or Adam Peaty and Matt Richards in the pool, but such are the fine margins in which the golds are decided.\", \"from\": 3478, \"to\": 3715, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3563, \"end\": 3567, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\", \"score\": 0.9965603685167485, \"rank\": 0.0032620324018940027, \"text\": \"Josh\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\"}, {\"begin\": 3612, \"end\": 3622, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Peaty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\"}, {\"begin\": 3627, \"end\": 3640, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Richards_(footballer,_born_1984)\", \"score\": 0.8167390230814645, \"rank\": 0.2243767313019458, \"text\": \"Matt Richards\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Richards_(footballer,_born_1984)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Richards_(footballer,_born_1984)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a slight nagging sense\", \"from\": 3497, \"to\": 3519}, {\"ngram\": \"the ones\", \"from\": 3523, \"to\": 3531}, {\"ngram\": \"the likes\", \"from\": 3550, \"to\": 3559}, {\"ngram\": \"Matt Hudson-Smith\", \"from\": 3577, \"to\": 3594}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 3598, \"to\": 3607}, {\"ngram\": \"the pool\", \"from\": 3644, \"to\": 3652}, {\"ngram\": \"the fine margins\", \"from\": 3667, \"to\": 3683}, {\"ngram\": \"the golds\", \"from\": 3693, \"to\": 3702}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While not quite bombastic, there was a feeling of positivity from within the British camp following medals across 18 different sports.\", \"from\": 3717, \"to\": 3851, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3794, \"end\": 3806, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Camp\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British camp\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Camp\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Camp\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a feeling\", \"from\": 3754, \"to\": 3763}, {\"ngram\": \"positivity\", \"from\": 3767, \"to\": 3777}, {\"ngram\": \"medals\", \"from\": 3817, \"to\": 3823}, {\"ngram\": \"18 different sports\", \"from\": 3831, \"to\": 3850}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Andy Anson, CEO of the British Olympic Association, said: \\\"I think the breadth of success is incredibly important in terms of the resonance it has around the country - 65 medals is a brilliant achievement.\", \"from\": 3853, \"to\": 4058, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3853, \"end\": 3863, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Anson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Andy Anson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Anson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Anson\"}, {\"begin\": 3876, \"end\": 3903, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British Olympic Association\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"CEO\", \"from\": 3865, \"to\": 3868}, {\"ngram\": \"the breadth\", \"from\": 3920, \"to\": 3931}, {\"ngram\": \"success\", \"from\": 3935, \"to\": 3942}, {\"ngram\": \"terms\", \"from\": 3970, \"to\": 3975}, {\"ngram\": \"the resonance\", \"from\": 3979, \"to\": 3992}, {\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 4007, \"to\": 4018}, {\"ngram\": \"65 medals\", \"from\": 4021, \"to\": 4030}, {\"ngram\": \"a brilliant achievement\", \"from\": 4034, \"to\": 4057}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But it's frustrating to be seventh in the medal table.\\\"\", \"from\": 4059, \"to\": 4114, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the medal table\", \"from\": 4097, \"to\": 4112}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But there was the glory snatched at the last minute, too: Alex Yee reeling in Hayden Wilde in the men's triathlon; and the women's quadruple sculls clawing back a deficit to win, aptly both golden moments happening within a few minutes of each other.\", \"from\": 4116, \"to\": 4366, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4174, \"end\": 4182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alex Yee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the glory\", \"from\": 4130, \"to\": 4139}, {\"ngram\": \"the last minute\", \"from\": 4152, \"to\": 4167}, {\"ngram\": \"Hayden Wilde\", \"from\": 4194, \"to\": 4206}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's triathlon\", \"from\": 4210, \"to\": 4229}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's quadruple sculls\", \"from\": 4235, \"to\": 4263}, {\"ngram\": \"a deficit\", \"from\": 4277, \"to\": 4286}, {\"ngram\": \"aptly both golden moments\", \"from\": 4295, \"to\": 4320}, {\"ngram\": \"a few minutes\", \"from\": 4338, \"to\": 4351}]}, {\"sentence\": \"How does Los Angeles now follow Paris in four years' time?\", \"from\": 4368, \"to\": 4426, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4377, \"end\": 4388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.751841119829654e-15, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 4400, \"end\": 4405, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4495731047582816e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"four years' time\", \"from\": 4409, \"to\": 4425}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We had a brief insight with a dusting of Hollywood gold, as Tom Cruiseabseiled off the roof of the Stade de Franceinto the closing ceremony and bands like the Red Hot Chili Peppers performed on LA's Venice Beach.\", \"from\": 4427, \"to\": 4639, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4468, \"end\": 4477, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1520276002202648e-14, \"text\": \"Hollywood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 4586, \"end\": 4607, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Hot_Chili_Peppers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Red Hot Chili Peppers\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q215380\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Hot_Chili_Peppers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Hot_Chili_Peppers\"}, {\"begin\": 4626, \"end\": 4638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venice,_Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999752494663, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Venice Beach\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venice,_Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venice,_Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a brief insight\", \"from\": 4434, \"to\": 4449}, {\"ngram\": \"a dusting\", \"from\": 4455, \"to\": 4464}, {\"ngram\": \"Tom\", \"from\": 4487, \"to\": 4490}, {\"ngram\": \"the roof\", \"from\": 4510, \"to\": 4518}, {\"ngram\": \"the Stade de Franceinto\", \"from\": 4522, \"to\": 4545}, {\"ngram\": \"the closing ceremony\", \"from\": 4546, \"to\": 4566}, {\"ngram\": \"bands\", \"from\": 4571, \"to\": 4576}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For now, we should simply be grateful to Paris.\", \"from\": 4641, \"to\": 4688, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4682, \"end\": 4687, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4495731047582816e-26